---
import InteractiveMockup from '../components/InteractiveMockup.jsx';
---

<section class="relative py-24 px-6 border-b border-white/5 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Clean, Lighter Background Accent for "Design" feel -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-1/2 h-full bg-gradient-to-l from-white/5 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>
    
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-16 relative z-10">
        
        <!-- Text Content -->
        <div class="flex-1 space-y-8">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-slate-300 text-xs font-mono">
                <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-white rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
                ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS
            </div>

            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">
                How much JavaScript should you ship?
            </h2>

            <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
                <p>
                    In a traditional application, the entire page is wrapped in JavaScript. 
                    Even the static footer pays the hydration tax.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong class="text-astro text-xl">Islands Architecture</strong> changes the equation. 
                    We carve out the interactive bits—share buttons, comments, carousels—and 
                    let the rest of the page be pure, lightweight HTML.
                </p>
            </div>

            <ul class="space-y-3 font-mono text-sm text-slate-300 mt-4">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-astro rounded-full"></div>
                    Header & Footer → 0kb JS
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-astro rounded-full"></div>
                    Article Text → 0kb JS
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-white">
                    <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-green-400 rounded-full shadow-[0_0_8px_#4ade80]"></div>
                    Interactivity → Loaded On-Demand
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Island -->
        <div class="flex-1 w-full">
            <!-- Glass container for the island -->
            <div class="p-2 rounded-3xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm">
                <InteractiveMockup client:visible />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>